   private Class<?> getMacroDefinitionHandlerClass() throws ClassNotFoundException

   {

       return loadClass("com.atlassian.confluence.xhtml.api.MacroDefinitionHandler");

   }
{code}
The loadClass method will eventuate to a lock being held, and during re-indexing this causes contention. A better strategy would be to use a LazyReference and only load the class once and then return the loaded class every time it is requested rather than re-loading it every time it is needed.

